records.addlTxt:
Defendant Brian J Heywood in court with attorney Peter M Wolff.  Abbey Nickolie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Plea Colloquy.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 3.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Couns 1 and 2 are dismissed and read in.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

90 Days Jail (First 20 days Straight Time.  Remaining Huber with Standard Release Conditions)  Consecutive to 14CT1973

Term of Probation: 2 Years

Conditions of Probation:
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Perform  20 hours of community service each year of probation 4-1-17;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
-Defendant is not to enter any premises that primarily serves alcohol;
- No contact with Waukesha Cab and Tonya  K.

Costs: $243.00   
(To be paid at the rate of $100.00  per month commencing 8-1-15. Failure to pay the Court orders 10 days Huber as contempt for non-compliance with Court Order).
